# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# learning-style-space.form — the auto-ml weave: every learning style
# is a data row, and the research loop discovers the bias a task wants
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The ask (2026-06-11): weave CNN, transformer, Euclidean, non-Euclidean,
# GDL, mesh, federated — every form of learning — into the auto-ml /
# auto-research lane so it combines and tries any form of learning in
# the most expansive, playful, alive way.
#
# The north-star shape: a learning STYLE is not code. It is a row of
# data — (id, pool, core) — dropped into ONE engine:
#
#     core : float signal → float signal    the MIXING (identity,
#            attention, mesh diffusion, ...)
#     pool : float signal → float features  the SYMMETRY (what stays
#            invariant: shift-pooled ring stats, chart sums, value
#            statistics, sorted spectrum, max-plus value, ...)
#     feature = quantize(pool(core(x)))     bins for nearest-shape
#
# Memory (la-intern), recognition (ns-sim bin-match), scoring
# (learning-arc's warmed predict-then-learn fold), selection (receipts
# → best), curiosity (least-tried-first), and federation (memories
# compose) are SHARED tissue. The inductive bias lives entirely in the
# row — so styles compose (any pool × any core), and a new bias is an
# appended row, never an engine change.
#
# SHIPPED: `form/form-stdlib/learning-style-space.fk` +
# `tests/learning-style-space-band.fk` → 4095 (12 claims), three-way
# (Go/Rust/TS), composing transformer-numerics + geometric-learning +
# nearest-shape + learning-arc.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What the band proves
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Three tasks, three DIFFERENT winners — the no-free-lunch fact is the
# structural reason the space must stay open and playful:
#
#   shift  task (same multiset both classes, shifted at eval)
#          → conv wins 4/4; raw 1 — translation symmetry pays exactly
#   chart  task (prism one-hot seeds labeled by chart)
#          → mesh wins 4/4 from ONE example per class; raw 0 —
#            the right pooling IS generalization
#   perm   task (distinct multisets, rearranged so extreme edges collide)
#          → attn wins 4/4; conv blinded to 2 — value statistics
#            where locality is blind
#
# And the aliveness claims:
#
#   totality     every row predicts through the one engine (bit 1)
#   no-free-lunch the three winners are pairwise distinct (bit 128)
#   composition  ("conv.attn" = conv pooling over attention mixing)
#                appended as data participates and scores 4 (bit 256)
#   openness     sortpool (order-free spectrum) appended as data is
#                perfect on the reflect task where raw and conv miss
#                (bit 512) — a bias the engine never knew, measurable
#                the moment its row lands
#   federation   two cells' half-memories score 5 and 4; merged scores
#                6 — collaboration strictly exceeds each alone (bit 1024)
#   curiosity    5 least-tried-first picks are 5 distinct styles — every
#                bias gets met before any is retried (bit 2048)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The map of learning families (the expansive part)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Rows that ride NOW (proven in this band):
#   dense / Euclidean-coordinate   raw row — quantized identity
#   CNN / translation              conv row — gl-ring-edges pooled
#   GDL / mesh / non-Euclidean     mesh row — gl-diffuse + chart pooling
#   transformer / attention        attn row — gl-attn-edges mixing
#   relational / RL                bell row — gl-value-iterate (max-plus)
#   order spectrum / permutation   sortpool row (the band's openness claim)
#   composition                    any pool × any core, as data
#
# Families already native in sibling tissue (the weave's outer loops):
#   evolutionary / genome search   autoresearch-loop.fk — mutate +
#                                  pareto frontier; THIS module's rows
#                                  are the genome it can now evolve
#   fitness-landscape walks        auto-fitness.fk — loss snapped to
#                                  parameter, mutator varies the param
#   promotion by proven count      champion-challenger.fk — authority
#                                  flips only on earned competition
#   online prototype learning      learning-arc.fk — the scoring fold
#   oracle distillation            co-learning.fk (0→91% measured)
#   federated merge                slice-merge.fk (sign-election,
#                                  deterministic) + ls-merge here
#   ensembles                      ensemble-vote.fk,
#                                  confidence-weighted-vote.fk
#   sequence / Markov              markov-2.fk, sequence-predictor.fk
#   novelty / honest unknown       novelty.fk — below the recognition
#                                  floor is a discovery, not a match
#   active inference               active-inference.fk
#   choice-receipt learning        choice-receipt-learning.fk — the
#                                  loop remembering which choices paid
#   weight training / gradient     metabolic-learning.fk — mtb-step
#                                  trains gl-engine edge weights
#                                  (credit → gift → release; SGD/Adam/
#                                  meta-learning as dial settings;
#                                  mtb-learn meta-tunes its own focus)
#
# Open stones with NAMED paths (not built ahead of need):
#   trained rows                   a style row whose pool/core carry
#                                  mtb-learned weights — metabolic-
#                                  learning's output becoming row data
#   tensor-scale autodiff          mtb-reverse's adjoint carried onto
#                                  the JIT emitter lane (jit-tensor-emit)
#   contrastive / self-supervised  pair-loss over ls-features — needs
#                                  only a loss row, no new engine
#   Hebbian / local plasticity     co-occurrence bumps on gl edge
#                                  weights — edges as memory
#   Bayesian / probabilistic       proven-count gates → priors
#                                  (classifier-eval's spine)
#   generative diffusion           ml-diffusion-model-flow.form — the
#                                  reverse flow; the OTHER diffusion
#   hypernetworks                  recipes emitting recipes — the
#                                  Hati-OS emit lane already
#                                  emits walkers; weights are next
#   reservoir computing            one row away: a fixed scramble core
#                                  + any pool (the engine is ready)
#   neural ODE / continuous flow   gl-diffuse's continuum limit
#   meta-learning                  the loop learning explore-order
#                                  from its own receipts — curiosity
#                                  becoming taste
#
# The teaching: expansive is not exhaustive. The space stays alive
# because (1) no row is privileged — no free lunch is a checked fact,
# (2) the curiosity floor guarantees every bias gets met, (3) new
# biases arrive as data while the engine holds still, and (4) the
# outer loops (evolve, promote, retire, distill, federate) are the
# same proven tissue whatever rows the genome carries.
#
# MEASURED AGAINST ACTUAL MODELS (experiments/fewshot-digits-ab,
# 2026-06-11): on real handwritten digits (sklearn, 5 seeds), the
# body's learner — exemplar interning + class prototypes (gl-mean
# readout) + −L2² graded similarity (the Gaussian weigh) + the
# translation ORBIT (GDL symmetry acted on memory), one pass, no
# gradients — beats the strongest of {1-NN, logistic regression,
# SGD-MLP, RBF-SVM} at every N from 10 to 500 (+2.7 pp at N=10,
# +2.3 at N=50), conceding only N=1000 to the Gaussian kernel
# machine (−0.4). Reaches 85% by N=50 where the SVM needs ~100 and
# the MLP ~200 — 2–4× fewer samples to criterion than the gradient
# path. Round 1 of the same experiment proved the style-space
# selection picks the right featurizer from the training stream
# alone. The kernel-band slice (predictions three-way, baselines as
# pinned references) is the named next stone.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Kinship
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   geometric-learning.form     the cores and pools — one semiring-
#                               generic gather; this module is its
#                               styles-as-data face
#   metabolic-learning.form     training over the same engine — the
#                               weights inside a future trained row
#   form-native-models.form     M7 names auto-ml as a Form meta-learner;
#                               this module is M7's style-space organ —
#                               the genome autoresearch evolves is now
#                               rows, not hand-picked candidates
#   autoresearch-runtime.form   genome / evaluator / experiment /
#                               governance — the loop these rows feed
#   federated-slices.form       the trainer axis at mesh scale
